.s3
.it Ioinfo
is a routine which obtains all input from the user's command line.
It is used in conjunction will picture handling.
.s3
If
.it argc
is less than
.it min,
.it msg
is printed to the error output file and execution stops.
.it msg
should be the usage line for the execution of a program.
Otherwise,
.it iw[0],
.it iw[1],
.it iw[2],
.it iw[3],
.it ci,
.it ri,
.it shift
and
.it size
are initially set to 1,1,1024,1024,1,1,0 and 4, respectively.
If
.it ifile
does not begin with "/dev", then the input picture file is assumed
to be on disk.  The header information is read from
.it ifile
and
.it iw[2]
.it iw[3]
and
.it size
are set to the actual picture header.
If
.it ifile
begins
will "/dev", the input file is assumed to be a system device and is
let alone.
.it ofile
is then swapped to contain the second argument of the command line.
All of the remaining arguments on the command line
are copied to their respective parameters, provided the arguments exist.
If they do not, they retain their default values.
